						<summary>

						<p>Stone near the Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI 11-12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription referring itself to the reign of Tribhuvanamalladeva is dated in the cyclic year [Vi]kāri, Uttarāyaṇa-saṅkrānti. The date is not verifiable.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a donation made by Ballaya Chōḷa-Mahārāja.</p>						

						</summary>
